# Network Sniffer — CodeAlpha Internship Task 1

A basic network packet sniffer built with Python using the Scapy library.

## What it does
- Captures live network traffic packets
- Displays source and destination IP addresses
- Shows protocol type (TCP, UDP, ICMP)
- Shows port numbers and TCP flags
- Prints a preview of the packet payload

## Files
- `network_sniffer.py` — main sniffer script

## Requirements
```bash
pip install scapy
```

## How to Run
```bash
sudo python3 network_sniffer.py
```
> Note: Root/admin privileges are required for packet capturing.

## Tech Used
- Python 3
- Scapy

